Text.Value: Then show the symbol the Justice granted you.
I have not.
An Amulet of the Dread Lord's likeness. Simple for his spawn to acquire.
I have proven my faith to the Tribunal. I'm an Unholy Assassin of Bhaal.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Skull assesses the viability after this.

Text.Value: Leave.
How could I prove my faith?
You lie. You are not faithful. The door stays closed.
Here - the Amulet of Bhaal.
A new vessel brimming with blood darkens Bhaal's door - to baptise his dais most holy.
Then you must know the way. Present the symbol, proof of your Father's favour.
Do you have proof of your faith to our lord?
I'm one of Bhaal's Unholy Assassins.
Bhaal created me above all others. Open for his prodigy!
How can I prove myself?
Present the symbol, noble spawn.
Proof of faith, held in worthy hands. It is as the Dread Lord requires.
Father says it's my turn at the Temple. Let me in!
*A rush of ancient whispers fills your mind as you approach the door. It is rife with magic - old, deathly magic.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: As if the skull is bored - like someone repeating a script for the millionth time.

Text.Value: I have an Amulet of Bhaal - let me pass, door.
The vessel returns, most shamefully unleaking. Prove your faith.
What symbol?
Worthy hands hold proof of faith - as the Dread Lord desires.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext:
I'm putting the "person approvals" under one bracket for brevity, For clarity all of these pass the same check, where you can have:

- Persuaded/deceived the skull into approving you as a person
- Be the Dark Urge
- Be the Unholy Assassin

Text.Value: Walk in blood.
I don't have the symbol on me.
Then shut this door shall stay.
You must bear proof of the Dread Lord's favour - or pay His toll of blood.
The truth is heard, and it pleases Him. The door will part.
The spill of murderous loins approaches once more. Show a proof of faith, spillage.
You hold proof of faith - but to hold and deserve are different. How have you proven yourself in the Dread Lord's eyes?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Cowed, realising they probably shouldn't have been irreverent

Text.Value: The faithful know.
I slaughtered the murder tribunal.
Then you will show the symbol granted by the Justice.
It has shown its worth, the door will part. Walk in blood.
Unorthodox - but a show of faith nonetheless.

Synopsis: A door blocking the entrance to the Bhaal section of the undercity ruins. Being rewritten - It was originally a skull, so it probably doesn't fit a door, but the original idea was to give it a little irreverance for characterisation.
